{"word":"διαμαρτυρέω","slug":"διαμαρτυρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>διαμαρτυρέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>as attic law-term, <i>to use a</i> <el>διαμαρτυρία</el> (<a href='S:quod vide'>q. <a href='S:vide'>v.</a></a>), <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to affirm by a</i> <el>διαμαρτυρία</el> <i>that</i> a thing is, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>τὰ διαμαρτυρηθέντα</el> <i>things so affirmed</i>, <b><a href='S:Isocrates'>Isocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}